Summary: This section details the methods and enumerations available for the PhysicalBone3D class, including applying impulses and defining joint types.

Method: _integrate_forces(state: PhysicsDirectBodyState3D)
Method: apply_central_impulse(impulse: Vector3)
Method: apply_impulse(impulse: Vector3, position: Vector3 = Vector3(0, 0, 0))
Method: get_bone_id() -> int
Method: get_simulate_physics() -> bool
Method: is_simulating_physics() -> bool

Enumerations
enum DampMode:
DAMP_MODE_COMBINE = 0: In this mode, the body's damping value is added to any value set in areas or the default value.
DAMP_MODE_REPLACE = 1: In this mode, the body's damping value replaces any value set in areas or the default value.

enum JointType:
JOINT_TYPE_NONE = 0: No joint is applied to the PhysicalBone3D.
JOINT_TYPE_PIN = 1: A pin joint is applied to the PhysicalBone3D.
JOINT_TYPE_CONE = 2: A cone joint is applied to the PhysicalBone3D.
JOINT_TYPE_HINGE = 3: A hinge joint is applied to the PhysicalBone3D.
JOINT_TYPE_SLIDER = 4: A slider joint is applied to the PhysicalBone3D.
JOINT_TYPE_6DOF = 5: A 6 degrees of freedom joint is applied to the PhysicalBone3D.
