Document: PhysicalBone3D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicalbone3d.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of the PhysicalBone3D node, including damping, velocity, transforms, physical material properties, and integration settings.

angular_damp (float): Damps the body's rotation. Default: 0.0. By default, the body will use the ProjectSettings.physics/3d/default_angular_damp project setting or any value override set by an Area3D the body is in. Depending on angular_damp_mode, you can set angular_damp to be added to or to replace the body's damping value. See ProjectSettings.physics/3d/default_angular_damp for more details about damping.
Method: set_angular_damp(value: float)
Method: get_angular_damp()

angular_damp_mode (DampMode): Defines how angular_damp is applied. Default: 0.
Method: set_angular_damp_mode(value: DampMode)
Method: get_angular_damp_mode()

angular_velocity (Vector3): The PhysicalBone3D's rotational velocity in radians per second. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).
Method: set_angular_velocity(value: Vector3)
Method: get_angular_velocity()

body_offset (Transform3D): Sets the body's transform. Default: Transform3D(1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0).
Method: set_body_offset(value: Transform3D)
Method: get_body_offset()

bounce (float): The body's bounciness. Default: 0.0. Values range from 0 (no bounce) to 1 (full bounciness). Note: Even with bounce set to 1.0, some energy will be lost over time due to linear and angular damping. To have a PhysicalBone3D that preserves all its energy over time, set bounce to 1.0, linear_damp_mode to DAMP_MODE_REPLACE, linear_damp to 0.0, angular_damp_mode to DAMP_MODE_REPLACE, and angular_damp to 0.0.
Method: set_bounce(value: float)
Method: get_bounce()

can_sleep (bool): If true, the body is deactivated when there is no movement, so it will not take part in the simulation until it is awakened by an external force. Default: true.
Method: set_can_sleep(value: bool)
Method: is_able_to_sleep()

custom_integrator (bool): If true, the standard force integration (like gravity or damping) will be disabled for this body. Default: false. Other than collision response, the body will only move as determined by the _integrate_forces() method, if that virtual method is overridden. Setting this property will call the method PhysicsServer3D.body_set_omit_force_integration() internally.
Method: set_use_custom_integrator(value: bool)
Method: is_using_custom_integrator()

friction (float): The body's friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (max friction). Default: 1.0.
Method: set_friction(value: float)
Method: get_friction()

gravity_scale (float): This is multiplied by ProjectSettings.physics/3d/default_gravity to produce this body's gravity. Default: 1.0. For example, a value of 1.0 will apply normal gravity, 2.0 will apply double the gravity, and 0.5 will apply half the gravity to this body.
Method: set_gravity_scale(value: float)
Method: get_gravity_scale()

joint_offset (Transform3D): Sets the joint's transform. Default: Transform3D(1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0).
Method: set_joint_offset(value: Transform3D)
Method: get_joint_offset()

joint_rotation (Vector3): Sets the joint's rotation in radians. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).
Method: set_joint_rotation(value: Vector3)
Method: get_joint_rotation()

joint_type (JointType): Sets the joint type. Default: 0.
Method: set_joint_type(value: JointType)
Method: get_joint_type()

linear_damp (float): Damps the body's movement. Default: 0.0. By default, the body will use ProjectSettings.physics/3d/default_linear_damp or any value override set by an Area3D the body is in. Depending on linear_damp_mode, linear_damp may be added to or replace the body's damping value. See ProjectSettings.physics/3d/default_linear_damp for more details about damping.
Method: set_linear_damp(value: float)
Method: get_linear_damp()

linear_damp_mode (DampMode): Defines how linear_damp is applied. Default: 0.
Method: set_linear_damp_mode(value: DampMode)
Method: get_linear_damp_mode()

linear_velocity (Vector3): The body's linear velocity in units per second. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0). Can be used sporadically, but don't set this every frame, because physics may run in another thread and runs at a different granularity. Use _integrate_forces() as your process loop for precise control of the body state.
Method: set_linear_velocity(value: Vector3)
Method: get_linear_velocity()

mass (float): The body's mass. Default: 1.0.
Method: set_mass(value: float)
Method: get_mass()
